De Lille is the only non-ANC MP in Cabinet. #Dstv403 JOHANNESBURG - Newly-appointed Public Works and Infrastructure Minister Patricia de Lille says the DA must leave her alone. DA leader Mmusi Maimane is describing her appointment as a well-orchestrated plan by the ANC. WATCH: De Lille appointment a 'well-executed ANC campaign': Maimane De Lille says Maimane should rather focus on what's wrong with his own party. "I really feel sorry for Mmusi Maimane. Please can you just leave me alone and continue saving your own life in the DA," the minister said.